    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hi Vincent\n\nSo basically my app is being used in a matching system. The user will search for suitable matches and be presented by a limited amount of information. However in the results, say for example the result matched on 'eye colour'. I want to display the this is why this particular hit was presented. This is how I'd like it to work...\n\n```\n<div class=\"hit\">\n    <div class=\"resultReason\">@{{#helpers.highlightResults}}@{{{ _highlightResult }}}@{{/helpers.highlightResults}}</div>\n    <div class=\"result\">\n        <p>Name: @{{ fname }} @{{ lname }}</p>\n        <p>Email: @{{ email }}</p>\n        <p>Town: @{{ town }}</p>\n        <p>Age: @{{ age }}</p>\n        <a href=\"/profile/@{{ id }}\">Full Profile</a>\n    </div>\n</div>\n\n\n<script>\n//\n//SEARCH CODE ETC\n//\n\nsearch.templatesConfig.helpers.highlightResults = function (text, render){\n    //loop through _highlightResult\n    //\n    //Create Message\n    var message = \"<div>This result was matched on:\" + _highlightResult.title;\n    //add to hit result\n    return message;\n}\n</script>\n```\n",
