    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Ok thanks for clarification. You can use the hits option.transformData.item: function(item) {} to add any pre-computed data (where you would have done your loop inside) to the item and then access it.\n\nFor example:\n\n``` js\nvar hits = instantsearch.widget.hits({\n  transformData: {\n    item: function(item) {\n      item.matchedData = ...\n      return item;\n    }\n  }\n});\n```\n\nThen in your template, use item.matchedData.\n\nAs for helpers, you need to use them like this:\n\n``` js\nsearch.templatesConfig.helpers.highlightResults = function (text, render){\n  var data = render(text);\n  return modifiedData(data)\n}\n```\n\nTo get the actual data object you need to call render on the passed text, this is a bit weird but how hogan.js (our template engine) works with helpers.\n\nPlease close the issue if it's ok.\n",
